  <h1>University of California, Los Angeles</h1>
  <h2>RESEARCH INFORMATION SHEET<br>Data Perception Study</h2>

  <h3>Introduction</h3>
  <p>
    Professor Rachit Dubey from the Department of Communication at the University of California, Los Angeles is conducting a research study. 
    You were selected as a possible participant because you are 18 years of age or older, fluent in English, and based in the U.S. 
    Your participation in this study is voluntary.
  </p>

  <h3>What should I know about this study?</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Someone will explain this research study to you.</li>
    <li>Whether or not you take part is up to you.</li>
    <li>You can choose not to take part or withdraw later without penalty.</li>
    <li>Your decision will not affect your relationship with UCLA.</li>
    <li>You can ask any questions you want before you decide.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Why is this research being done?</h3>
  <p>
    The purpose of this study is to better understand how people process information, make judgments, and solve problems.
    The findings may help us gain insight into human cognition and behavior.
  </p>

  <h3>How long will it take, and what will I do?</h3>
  <p>
    Participation will take about 10–12 minutes. You will read instructions, complete computer-based tasks, and answer short questions
    about your perceptions and opinions of the data you viewed.
  </p>

  <h3>Risks and Benefits</h3>
  <p>
    There are no anticipated risks or discomforts beyond everyday experiences. You may withdraw at any time.
    There are no direct benefits, but the research may advance understanding of human cognition.
  </p>

  <h3>Confidentiality</h3>
  <p>
    Data will be collected anonymously and stored on secure, password-protected servers. No identifying information will be linked to your responses.
    Only the research team and authorized UCLA personnel may access de-identified data.
  </p>

  <h3>Compensation</h3>
  <p>
    You will be compensated at a rate of at least $15 per hour via the study platform after completing the study.
  </p>

  <h3>Contact Information</h3>
  <p><strong>Researcher:</strong> Prof. Rachit Dubey — <a href="mailto:rdubey@ucla.edu">rdubey@ucla.edu</a></p>
  <p><strong>UCLA Office of Human Research Protection Program (OHRPP):</strong> (310) 206-2040, 
     <a href="mailto:participants@research.ucla.edu">participants@research.ucla.edu</a></p>

  <h3>Your Rights</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You can choose whether to participate or withdraw at any time.</li>
    <li>No penalty or loss of benefits for refusing to participate.</li>
    <li>You may skip any questions you don’t wish to answer.</li>
  </ul>

